 >>	After reading through past postings, comp. security.misc
 >>I find your name a an appropriate contact for advice on the best way to 
 >>post an announcement of a new technology development of international
 >>significance.

 >I'm touched. My recommendations: 

 >1) don't try a sales pitch on USENET - they *always* flop.
 >2) crosspost a *SINGLE* message to:

 >Newsgroups: comp.security.misc,alt.security,sci.crypt
 >^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

 >- by crosspost, I mean that you POST A SINGLE MESSAGE WHICH APPEARS IN
 >THREE GROUPS SIMULTANEOUSLY, rather than posting the same message three
 >times over, to individual groups.

 >The latter would be a gross breach of netiquette, and you'ld be laughed
 >at.


 >In order to crosspost correctly, and thus not to be laughed at, post
 >your message with the Newsgroups: line set to the above...

